Architecture plan for Issue #35: Change the app background to green

Project shape:
- Full-stack app with a Rust Axum backend in backend/ and a React/Vite frontend in frontend/.
- The backend serves JSON API routes under /api and serves the built Vite SPA/static assets for browser routes.
- Frontend styling is Tailwind CSS with utility classes embedded in React components plus global CSS in frontend/src/styles.css.
- Main route/component structure: frontend/src/App.tsx renders signed-out home, login/register routes, and PlannerShell for authenticated users. PlannerShell composes DayTimeline and ClientManager.

Implementation approach for Issue #35:
- This is a frontend-only visual change. No database, backend API, shared type, or migration changes are needed.
- Locate all app-level background classes currently using neutral/off-white colors (notably bg-stone-50 / bg-white where appropriate) in App.tsx and planner/auth components.
- Prefer a consistent green background at the outer page containers so every route changes without disrupting cards/forms. Keep content panels readable by preserving white card backgrounds where needed.
- If the issue requires the entire app background rather than individual cards, update top-level <main> containers and any shared shell root only.

Validation:
- Run frontend build/typecheck with npm --prefix frontend run build.
- If available/needed, run Playwright or a browser check to confirm computed body/main background is green and pages still render meaningful content.
